=begin
	   Sail2 Version: 1.0.2 (April 12, 2026)

	   This Is A Go2 Style Script For OSA Shipboard Travel. Using The Oceandb, Sail2 Will
	   Sail Your Ship From Any Location In The Ocean To Any Other Using UIDs And Port Names.
	   Must Be Ran From Your Ship While Your Ship Is At Sea. First Time Users Must Run ;sail2 update
	   First To Download Appropriate Mapdb files.

	   Use:
	       ;sail2 <Port or UID>                        Will Begin Sailing To Destination.
	       ;sail2 <Port or UID> <Port or UID>          Will Display Step-by-step Route For Designated Travel.
	       ;sail2 update                               Will Check For Up-To-Date Ocean Mapdb files.
	   
	   Available Ports:
	   
	                   Brisker's Cove                  briskercove
	                   Glaoveln                        glaoveln
	                   Icemule Trace                   icemule
	                   Kraken's Fall                   kraken
	                   Wehnimer's Landing              landing
	                   Sleeping Drake Harbor           ornath
	                   Nielira Harbor                  nielira
	                   River's Rest                    riversrest
	                   Solhaven                        solhaven
	                   Teras Isle                      teras
	                   Ta'Vaalor                       vaalor
	                   Talon Isle                      talon
					   
	   Enjoy!
	
	   ~Peggyanne
	   
	   PS: feel free to send me any bugs via discord Bait#4376 and I'll try my best to fix them.
	 
	   Change Log:
	 
                March 7, 2026 - Initial Release. I'll Be Doing Cleanup On The Interface Over Time But All Should Be Functional.
               March 14, 2026 - Added Support For Getting Your Ship Underway For You. Added Update Support. (Removing Nautical-Charts-Update Dependancy)
               April 12, 2026 - Fixed Definition Issue For Ship Functions. Fixed UID Room Detection and Fixed Watch Ocean Issues.
=end 

i_stand_alone
require 'json'
require 'set'
require 'timeout'
require 'open-uri'
require 'fileutils'

# JSON Data
JSON_GIT_USER  = 'jmbreitfeld'
JSON_GIT_REPO  = 'OSA-Ocean-Database'
JSON_GIT_PATH  = ''
LOCAL_JSON_DIR = File.join(MAP_DIR, 'OSAMaps', 'Database')

def sync_echo(msg); respond "[MapSync: #{msg}]" rescue puts msg; end

def download_folder(user, repo, api_path, local_dir)
  FileUtils.mkdir_p(local_dir) unless Dir.exist?(local_dir)
  api_url = "https://api.github.com/repos/#{user}/#{repo}/contents/#{api_path}"
  
  begin
    # GitHub API requires a User-Agent header [cite: 26, 27]
    response = URI.open(api_url, "User-Agent" => "Lich-Map-Syncer").read
    data = JSON.parse(response)

    unless data.is_a?(Array)
      sync_echo("Error: #{api_path} in #{repo} is not a folder.")
      return 0
    end

    count = 0
    data.each do |file|
      next unless file['type'] == 'file' # Only download files, skip folders [cite: 30]
      
      file_name    = file['name']
      remote_size  = file['size'].to_i
      download_url = file['download_url']
      local_path   = File.join(local_dir, file_name)

      # Only download if file is missing or size has changed [cite: 31]
      if !File.exist?(local_path) || File.size(local_path) != remote_size
        sync_echo("Downloading: #{file_name} from #{repo}...")
        URI.open(download_url) do |remote|
          File.open(local_path, "wb") { |local| local.write(remote.read) }
        end
        count += 1
      end
    end
    count
  rescue => e
    sync_echo("Error syncing #{repo}/#{api_path}: #{e.message}")
    0
  end
end

def sync_all
  sync_echo("Connecting to GitHub APIs...")
  
  # 1. Sync the JSON data from the separate Git 
  json_updates = download_folder(JSON_GIT_USER, JSON_GIT_REPO, JSON_GIT_PATH, LOCAL_JSON_DIR)

  total = json_updates
  if total > 0
    sync_echo("Success! Updated #{total} files from one repository.")
  else
    sync_echo("All files are up to date.")
  end
end

